The paper presents a compressed representation of tries, which is a fundamental data structure in computer science. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The paper also discusses the worst-case optimal size of the compressed data structure, which is related to computational complexity, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of several interesting data structures, such as an optimal data structure for random access to a grammar-compressed string and an optimal data structure for a variant of the level ancestor problem, which are related to data mining (cs.DM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG).
